SIMPLE: lookout
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lookout
<hw>Look"out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
careful looking or watching for any object or event.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The place from which such observation is
made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A person engaged in watching; a sentinel; a
sentry.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Object or duty of forethought and care;
responsibility.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>on the lookout for</b></col> <cd>in search of; looking
for.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>look-over</ent>⟦br⟧
